File: A general view of the headquarters of Eskom. AFP/Gianluigi Guercia JOHANNESBURG -  Eskom will be implementing load reduction in KwaZulu Natal, Free State, Limpopo, and Mpumalanga on Sunday, to avoid network overloading in high-density areas. The power utility said load reduction will take place between 5 pm and 9 pm. READ: Eskom urges households to reduce electricity use Areas like eThekwini, Newcastle, and Nqutu in KZN will be affected by the power cuts. Provincial statements issued by Eskom the areas affected. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
